<paragraph id="8B8736D1FF2A9841CF024C11FCC2FBE7" blockId="6.[529,786,1091,1117]" box="[529,786,1091,1117]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">
<heading id="D0CF81BDFF2A9841CF024C11FCC2FBE7" box="[529,786,1091,1117]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CF024C11FCC2FBE7" authority="Priesner" authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1950" box="[529,786,1091,1117]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CF024C11FD7DFBE7" bold="true" box="[529,685,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">Eremiothrips</emphasis>
Priesner
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8736D1FF2A9841CDD34C2AFD20F9B4" blockId="6.[160,1156,1144,1550]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">
The eremophilous genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CCF34C2AFDB8FB2B" authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1950" box="[480,616,1144,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CCF34C2AFDB8FB2B" box="[480,616,1144,1169]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">Eremiothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently includes 21 species (ThripsWiki 2021). Most of these are known from southern Mediterranean countries (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B20FF2A9841CE824CC8FB83FB09" author="Bhatti JS &amp; Telmadarraiy Z &amp; Kumar V &amp; Tyagi K" box="[913,1107,1178,1203]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" pagination="49 - 110" refId="ref7589" refString="Bhatti JS, Telmadarraiy Z, Kumar V, Tyagi K. 2003. Species of Eremiothrips in Iran (Terebrantia: Thripidae). Thrips. 2: 49 - 110. doi: 10.46318 / Thrips. 2.2003.49 - 110" type="journal article" year="2003">Bhatti et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
; zur Strassen 2003), with 13 known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F32F7641FF2A9841CF694CEFFD75FB6C" box="[634,677,1213,1238]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B20FF2A9841CFA74CEFFCEFFB6C" author="Minaei K" box="[692,831,1213,1238]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref7772" refString="Minaei K. 2012. The genus Eremiothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) in Iran, with one new species. Zootaxa. 3349 (1): 56 - 62. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3349.1.6" type="journal article" year="2012">Minaei 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B20FF2A9841CE5E4CEFFC54FB6C" author="Minaei K" box="[845,900,1213,1238]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" pagination="29 - 34" refId="ref7811" refString="Minaei K. 2014. A new species of Eremiothrips from Iran (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Acta Entomol Musei Nationalis Pragae. 54 (1): 29 - 34." type="journal article" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B20FF2A9841CE814CEFFF07FB43" author="Minaei K &amp; Aleosfoor M" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" pagination="479 - 485" refId="ref7878" refString="Minaei K, Aleosfoor M. 2020. First description of the male Eremiothrips tamaricis (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). J Entomol Soc Iran. 39 (4): 479 - 485." type="journal article" year="2020">Minaei and Aleosfoor 2020</bibRefCitation>
), and a few known from 
<collectingCountry id="F32F7641FF2A9841CCE14CB2FDF9FB43" box="[498,553,1248,1273]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F32F7641FF2A9841CF704CB2FD73FB43" box="[611,675,1248,1273]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B20FF2A9841CFA24CB2FCECFB43" author="Minaei K" box="[689,828,1248,1273]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref7772" refString="Minaei K. 2012. The genus Eremiothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) in Iran, with one new species. Zootaxa. 3349 (1): 56 - 62. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3349.1.6" type="journal article" year="2012">Minaei 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The desert climate of 
<collectingCountry id="F32F7641FF2A9841C9564CB2FF38FAA1" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
seems favourable for this genus. The members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CE364D50FC7DFAA1" authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1950" box="[805,941,1282,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CE364D50FC7DFAA1" box="[805,941,1282,1307]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">Eremiothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognised by the following features: antennae 9-segmented (
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CFDC4D77FCF8FA84" box="[719,808,1317,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhatti">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CFDC4D77FCF8FA84" box="[719,808,1317,1342]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">E. bhatti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CE4E4D77FC0CFA84" baseAuthorityName="Priesner" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[861,988,1317,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="efflatouni">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CE4E4D77FC0CFA84" box="[861,988,1317,1342]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">E. efflatouni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
8-segmented); sense cones on antennal segments III and IV forked (simple in 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CE5F4D1AFC6BFADB" authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1950" box="[844,955,1352,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitator">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CE5F4D1AFC6BFADB" box="[844,955,1352,1377]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">E. imitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); head wider than long; pronotum with 1 pair of posteroangular setae (
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CFEE4D38FCAFFA39" baseAuthorityName="Priesner" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[765,895,1386,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="efflatouni">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CFEE4D38FCAFFA39" box="[765,895,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">E. efflatouni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CEA84D38FBF3FA39" authorityName="Minaei" authorityYear="2014" box="[955,1059,1386,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eshghii">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CEA84D38FBF3FA39" box="[955,1059,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">E. eshghii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without setae); tergites and sternites of abdomen without craspeda. Males with or without pore plates on sternites, tergite IX with special paired processes present or absent (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B20FF2A9841C9174DE2FF07FA51" author="Bhatti JS &amp; Telmadarraiy Z &amp; Kumar V &amp; Tyagi K" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" pagination="49 - 110" refId="ref7589" refString="Bhatti JS, Telmadarraiy Z, Kumar V, Tyagi K. 2003. Species of Eremiothrips in Iran (Terebrantia: Thripidae). Thrips. 2: 49 - 110. doi: 10.46318 / Thrips. 2.2003.49 - 110" type="journal article" year="2003">Bhatti et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B20FF2A9841CDF74D80FEBEFA51" author="Minaei K" box="[228,366,1490,1515]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" pagination="29 - 34" refId="ref7811" refString="Minaei K. 2014. A new species of Eremiothrips from Iran (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Acta Entomol Musei Nationalis Pragae. 54 (1): 29 - 34." type="journal article" year="2014">Minaei 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D52FF2A9841CCEF4D80FD54FA51" authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1950" box="[508,644,1490,1515]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CEAC3FF2A9841CCEF4D80FD54FA51" box="[508,644,1490,1515]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1605">Eremiothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are seemingly phytophagous on flowers and leaves and do not exhibit a specific host association.
</paragraph>
